pipeline_summary.name: Portfolio Rebalancing DAG
pipeline_summary.description: Implements a financial portfolio rebalancing pipeline using a fanout/fanin pattern with 5 parallel brokerage data fetches, analysis, aggregation and trade order generation.

components.name: Fetch Brokerage Holdings
components.description: Retrieves mock holdings CSV data for a given brokerage account via a simulated API call.
outputs: holdings_data (object)  dictionary with brokerage ID and holdings list

components.name: Analyze Portfolio
components.description: Calculates portfolio metrics such as total value, allocation percentages, and risk score for each brokerage's holdings.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after its corresponding fetch_brokerage_holdings task succeeds

components.name: Aggregate and Rebalance
components.description: Aggregates analysis results from all brokerages and computes the set of rebalancing trades needed to meet target allocations.
inputs: analysis_results_list (list<object>)  outputs of all analyze_portfolio tasks
outputs: rebalancing_trades (list<object>)  trade specifications with symbol, action, amount, and allocation

upstream_policy.description: Executes after all analyze_portfolio tasks have completed successfully

components.name: Generate Trade Orders
components.description: Creates a timestamped CSV file containing the final trade orders derived from the rebalancing calculation.
outputs: trade_orders_csv (file)  CSV file with trade instructions

description.default: Implements a financial portfolio rebalancing pipeline using a fanout/fanin pattern with 5 parallel brokerage data fetches, analysis, aggregation and trade order generation.

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

brokerage_id.description: Identifier of the brokerage account to fetch holdings for
brokerage_id.constraints: Must be one of: BROKERAGE_001, BROKERAGE_002, BROKERAGE_003, BROKERAGE_004, BROKERAGE_005

holdings_data.description: Holdings dictionary received from the corresponding fetch_brokerage_holdings task

analysis_results.description: List of analysis result dictionaries from all analyze_portfolio tasks

rebalancing_trades.description: List of trade dictionaries produced by aggregate_and_rebalance

sources: Mock brokerage API providing holdings CSV data for each brokerage account (BROKERAGE_001005)
sinks: Local CSV file (trade_orders_YYYYMMDD.csv) containing the final rebalancing trade orders
intermediate_datasets: holdings_data_{brokerage_id}  dictionary of mock holdings per brokerage
rebalancing_trades  aggregated list of trades needed to meet target allocations
